九、課程其他要求 Other Requirements

In Class Grading: The In Class portion [20%] of the final grade will be calculated as follows   Minutes Absent              In Class Grade  0 - 29                         90 30 - 149                         85150 – 329                        80330 - 449                        70450 – 599                        50600 - 719                          0  > 719                        - 20No one missing more than 720 minutes of class will be allowed to pass the course regardless of the reason. The ‘In Class’ grades may be adjusted up (or down) by as much as 10% if the teacher feels that the student has made an effort far above (or below) the general level of the other students. If you hope to increase your grade try the following: Increasing Your Grade                                           Reducing Your Grade•Talk often                                                       •Don’t talk•Ask questions                                                    •Miss a lot of classes•Prepare before class                                             •Never prepare for class•Don’t be late or absent                                         •Arrive late often•Use only English                                                 •Speak Chinese in class  No Chinese Rule: If the teacher hearing you using Chinese in class you will receive a red ‘C’ and your ‘In Class’ grade will be reduced by 2%. The first three ‘Cs’ are free and will incur no penalty. Quizzes: Surprise vocabulary quizzes will be regularly given in class. These quizzes will cover any of the vocabulary lists given by the teacher. Students are urged to keep a notebook of the vocabulary and review it regularly. A total of four surprise quizzes will be given throughout the semester. 

